i’ve got a thing for monsters.

36
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,980
Want a demonstration?

37
00:01:23,050 --> 00:01:25,980
Come at me,
and i’ll take you all down.

38
00:01:26,050 --> 00:01:28,120
Let’s find out
who’s the strongest in here.

39
00:01:28,180 --> 00:01:30,920
Now don’t make me wait all day.
Bring it on.

40
00:01:30,990 --> 00:01:33,460
- Sitch: Cease this foolishness.
- Garou: Foolishness?

41
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:35,190
Sitch: We don’t need you.
Get lost.

42
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:37,560
Garou: I can’t believe
you treat your guests this way,

43
00:01:37,630 --> 00:01:39,630
Mr. Big shot of justice.

44
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,430
Let me show you how it’s done.

45
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:45,230
Each and every coward here
is cordially invited

46
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:47,540
to a little slaughter party.

47
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,970
Sitch: I’ve got a job
for you three heroes.

48
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:52,140
Toss this joker out.

49
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:53,680
Magicman: With pleasure.

50
00:01:58,110 --> 00:02:00,380
( Gags )

51
00:02:00,450 --> 00:02:03,490
( Heavy tank loincloth roars )

52
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:04,520
Huh?

53
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:06,350
Garou: Tough break, grandpa.

54
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:09,160
Looks like you forgot to put
some heart into that punch.

55
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:11,060
The only thing
that really matters

56
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:13,400
is that the strong are strong!

57
00:02:13,460 --> 00:02:16,170
Night-night, gramps!

58
00:02:16,230 --> 00:02:18,130
( Criminals laugh, chatter )

59
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,040
Criminal #2:
Now that’s how you do it!

60
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:21,970
Criminal #3: Hell, yeah!
You showed him!

61
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,340
- Garou: Huh?
- Criminal #4: All right!

62
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,510
Garou: What are you vermin
cheering about?

63
00:02:25,570 --> 00:02:27,210
You’re all gonna die, too.

64
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,940
Criminal #5: Wait.
What did you just say?!

65
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:31,180
Criminal #6: We’re supposed
to be on the same side here!

66
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:33,680
Garou: Not true. Heroes are
always late to the party,

67
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,520
while monsters
take the initiative.

68
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:39,020
They appear without warning,
out of the blue.

69
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:41,120
Listen up.
You’re on the humans’ side,

70
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:44,360
while i’m
on the monsters’ side.

71
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,660
Blue fire: A human
who calls himself a monster?

72
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:48,000
You’re delusional.

73
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:50,930
I’ll burn your body to ash!

74
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:58,410
( Winces )

75
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:00,910
Garou: These little tricks
certainly liven things up,

76
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:03,310
but once you see through them,
they’re ugly.

77
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:04,380
Blue fire: My arm!

78
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:05,510
Sitch: This is central tower,

79
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,380
seventh floor multipurpose hall.

80
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:11,320
Send every hero in the facility
to this location immediately,

81
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:12,320
all of them!

82
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,560
( Gasps )

83
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:18,890
Garou: Taking on a bunch
of class-s heroes at once?

84
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:21,460
That might be
a bit much right now.

85
00:03:21,530 --> 00:03:25,400
Well, i’m sure this pile
of bodies gets my point across.

86
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:28,070
Spectacular debut, huh?

87
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:30,510
Today was
my declaration of war.

88
00:03:30,570 --> 00:03:33,180
In six months,
i’ll be even stronger.

89
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:37,180
I’ll be using the front door
when I return.

90
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,950
