00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:52,250
Saitama: You don’t get
what it means to be a hero.

253
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,260
The world is chock-full

254
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,590
of super-strong
and pretty awful people.

255
00:09:56,660 --> 00:09:59,590
Standing up to them
is what heroes do,

256
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:02,230
even if that means
doing it alone.

257
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,170
This whole act is pathetic.

258
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:06,900
You surround yourself
with weaklings and kiss-asses

259
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:09,170
just so you can feel
like you might be strong.

260
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,270
These factions,
crushing the noobs,

261
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:14,340
that ranking stuff,
none of it matters.

262
00:10:14,410 --> 00:10:17,410
Show heroes some respect, poser!

263
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,510
Blizzard: Shut up!
You don’t know me!

264
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:21,280
You don’t know
anything about me!

265
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:23,250
( Rumbling )

266
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:26,450
♪

267
00:10:34,330 --> 00:10:35,700
( Grunts )

268
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,370
( Yells )

269
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,640
Saitama: Huh?

270
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:47,510
( Steam hissing )

271
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:50,650
( Rubble clattering )

272
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:52,280
( Blizzard groans )

273
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:53,650
What happ--

274
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:57,190
genos: Hmm, how curious.
My hunt for a rat

275
00:10:57,250 --> 00:11:00,620
seems to have led me
back to master’s apartment.

276
00:11:00,690 --> 00:11:01,960
( Blizzard gasps )

277
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:03,590
That’s genos, a class-s.

278
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:05,060
What’s he doing here?

279
00:11:05,130 --> 00:11:07,630
Genos:
Master saitama, apologies.

280
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,070
I kicked up some dust
around your home.

281
00:11:10,130 --> 00:11:13,140
Saitama: This is a little more
than some dust, genos!

282
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,500
Blizzard: Uh...

283
00:11:14,570 --> 00:11:17,440
Saitama: I caught a glimpse
of Sonic in the chaos.

284
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,680
What were the two of you doing?

285
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:22,110
Blizzard: You have connections
with class-s heroes?

286
00:11:22,180 --> 00:11:23,980
Saitama: Huh?
Oh, you mean genos?

287
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,350
Genos: I am
master saitama’s disciple.

288
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,480
Blizzard: His disciple?

289
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:30,350
But you outrank him.

290
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:33,960
Genos: You are a hero, class b,
rank one, hellish blizzard.

291
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,060
I see what is happening.

292
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,060
You have targeted master saitama

293
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:39,260
as your latest
newcomer hero to crush.

294
00:11:39,330 --> 00:11:41,560
But he is stronger
than anticipated,

295
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:44,130
and now you are near death
from fighting him, correct?

296
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,130
Saitama: Nah.

297
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,370
She just got caught up

298
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,100
in all that "dust kicking"
you were doing.

299
00:11:48,170 --> 00:11:50,110
Genos: My deepest apologies
if I was the cause

300
00:11:50,170 --> 00:11:51,640
- of any--
- Sonic: Exploding shuriken!

301
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,440
( Blizzard gasps ) A monster?

302
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:57,210
Saitama: Eh, not really.
This is gonna take a minute,

303
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,950
so you can go home if you want.

304
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,950
Genos: Hmph! You could throw
100 more of those things.

305
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:03,050
You would not harm me.

306
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,090
Sonic: Maybe,

307
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:05,650
but you haven’t even hit me...

308
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,960
Puppet-man.

309
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:11,390
Watch, saitama!

310
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:13,030
Bear witness!

311
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,360
After I turn your disciple
into scrap, you’re next!

312
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:18,900
Blizzard: Such intense hatred.
Even just standing there,

313
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:22,040
I can sense his extraordinary
combat ability.

314
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:24,140
He’s dangerous.

315
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:27,480
Genos: Master, this stalker’s
presence is an affront.

316
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:30,650
I will do the world a favor
and rid it of his existence.

317
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:34,220
( Sonic scoffs ) A slug like you
could never get rid of me.

318
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,680
You sure you still want to fight

319
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:37,590
when you’ve already shown me
all you’ve got?

320
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:40,560
Genos: When did I show you
all that I have got?

321
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:43,290
You lose, wretched fool.

322
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,360
Sonic: Huh? ( Gasps )

323
00:12:46,730 --> 00:12:49,600
♪

324
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,340
Genos: Accelerate.

325
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:01,610
Saitama: Wow.

326
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,180
Looks like he’s
gotten a little faster

327
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,480
since the last
time we sparred. Huh.

328
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:08,150
Maybe it’s an upgrade.

329
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:10,190
Blizzard: I can’t see a thing.

330
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:14,590
( Punches clanking )

331
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:21,100
Sonic: Why does he
keep going behind me?

332
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:24,300
Does this cocky child
think he’s faster than me?

333
00:13:27,570 --> 00:13:29,300
Genos: You had
some lint in your hair,

334
00:13:29,370 --> 00:13:30,370
but I picked it out.

335
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,610
Sonic: You little bastard!

336
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,550
Genos: As predicted,
you dropped your guard.

337
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:39,250
Machine gun blows!

338
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,680
He dodged it?

339
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,620
- Wait!
- ( Sonic laughs )

340
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:46,150
What a hopeless buffoon.

341
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:47,560
You sure talk a lot

342
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:50,330
for someone
who only manages to punch air.

343
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:52,460
This master technique
uses special footwork

344
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:55,560
and my super-fast movement
to create afterimages.

345
00:13:55,630 --> 00:13:58,170
It’s called fourfold funeral!

346
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:01,540
Now die. Scatter flash slash!

347
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,040
Genos: I cannot follow
his movement,

348
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,610
so I will lay waste
to this entire area.

349
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:10,450
Incineration cannons,
maximum intensity!

350
00:14:10,510 --> 00:14:11,550
Blizzard: It’s done!

351
00:14:12,610 --> 00:14:14,950
( Sonic gasps ) I won?

352
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,920
No, he dropped
before I slashed him.

353
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:19,090
What happened?

354
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,090
Saitama.

355
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,060
Trying to save your disciple?

356
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,460
You’re too soft.

357
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,400
Saitama: I’d just rather
my entire neighborhood

358
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:27,560
didn’t get blown to hell.

359
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:29,200
And, besides, the two of you

360
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:30,430
have no reason to fight.

361
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,130
- Hey, genos...
- ( Genos groaning )

362
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,140
Saitama: Were you built for
petty street fights like this?

363
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,470
And, Sonic,
I thought you were after me.

364
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:38,110
So, just this once,

365
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:40,040
i’m gonna
take you seriously, okay?

366
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:42,940
♪

367
00:14:43,010 --> 00:14:43,980
Come at me, bro.

368
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:47,380
Sonic: I’ve been waiting
for this moment,

369
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:51,020
and, to kill you, i’ve perfected
the ultimate technique!

370
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:52,690
Prepare yourself!

371
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:54,320
Saitama: Nice. I’m hyped.

372
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:56,360
Sonic:
Ultimate master technique!

373
00:14:56,430 --> 00:14:58,960
Tenfold funeral!

374
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:01,300
Genos: Ten clone afterimages?

375
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:03,630
Though a joke,
he must have trained hard.

376
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:05,600
Blizzard:
That maniac’s combat skills

377
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:07,600
are equivalent to a class-s.

378
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:11,170
A hero at saitama’s level
stands no chance against him.

379
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,540
Even so...

380
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:14,580
Sonic: Why do I feel
like i’m destined to lose

381
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:17,010
every single time I face you?

382
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:20,250
Until I can break that mentality
by beating you,

383
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,580
I will never reach
the next level.

384
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:25,350
Saitama: Killer move:
Serious series.

385
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,990
Serious sideways jumps!

386
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:31,990
( Sonic gags )

387
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:35,500
♪

388
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:39,440
What was that?

389
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,200
Saitama: I just
did some sideways jumps,

390
00:15:41,270 --> 00:15:42,540
but I guess I went too far.

391
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,240
Sonic: He beat me
with shock waves?

392
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:49,110
My technique was meaningless.
He was faster.

393
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:51,910
I swear, next time we...

394
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:53,450
Genos: Is he dead?

395
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:55,080
Saitama: I wasn’t
trying to kill him.

396
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:58,350
Blizzard: Such power.

397
00:15:59,420 --> 00:16:01,360
He’s not normal.

398
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:05,790
♪

399
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:08,600
I could never
make it to number one.

400
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:11,970
I had intelligence,
stamina, street smarts,

401
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:15,440
and I was fortunate enough
to be born an esper.

402
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:19,040
With those attributes,
I should be standing at the top.

403
00:16:19,110 --> 00:16:21,040
If only it weren’t for her...

404
00:16:22,110 --> 00:16:23,610
My older sister

405
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:27,450
and the world’s
most powerful esper, tornado.

406
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:31,190
Because of her,
I would never be number one

407
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:33,560
in anything my entire life.

408
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:35,690
There was no beating my sister.

409
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:39,460
So when I became class b,
rank one, I got to thinking.

410
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:41,730
If I remain in this position,

411
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,630
I could control
all the heroes below me

412
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:46,600
and, with them, gather
enough strength to surpass her.

413
00:16:46,670 --> 00:16:48,070
Genos: That little runt--

414
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:50,540
terrible tornado
is class s, though.

415
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:53,240
Why not simply aim
for class a, rank one?

416
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:54,810
Blizzard:
That’s out of the question.

417
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,480
While i’d have no problem

418
00:16:56,550 --> 00:17:00,050
climbing the ranks of class a,
i’d never be rank one,

419
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,820
not ever.

420
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,990
Class a, rank 4--bushi drill.

421
00:17:04,050 --> 00:17:06,620
Class a, rank 3--okama itachi.

422
00:17:06,690 --> 00:17:08,990
Class a, rank 2--iairon.

423
00:17:09,060 --> 00:17:10,890
Even these three swordsmen,

424
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:13,700
disciples of the class-s hero
atomic samurai,

425
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,700
cannot progress any further.

426
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,470
Why can’t
these worthy heroes advance?

427
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:20,570
One hero stands in their way,

428
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,040
class a, rank one--amai mask.

429
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:24,870
- ( Group screaming )
- Amai mask: There you are.

430
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:27,480
The primitive savage
who was found frozen in ice

431
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:29,650
and revived
by a miracle of science.

432
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:30,810
Suppon, right?

433
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,750
You escaped
from the research facility

434
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:34,720
and attacked those
who tried to help you.

435
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:36,750
You are evil and a menace.

436
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:39,850
The association asked me
to bring you in alive.

437
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,730
However, i’m simply
not that merciful.

438
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,160
( Suppon growls )

439
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,530
( Gags )

440
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,870
Amai mask: Enough, already!

441
00:17:56,570 --> 00:17:58,470
( Crowd cheering )

442
00:17:58,540 --> 00:18:01,110
Woman: Amai mask! ( Squeals )

443
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:02,810
♪

444
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,010
Blizzard: The world
is a dangerous place.

445
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,580
It’s plagued
with unimaginable monsters.

446
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:09,780
You’re quite
the monster yourself,

447
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:12,760
but not to the level
of amai mask or my sister.

448
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:15,590
There’s king,
who they call the strongest man,

449
00:18:15,660 --> 00:18:18,060
and, blast, who stands
atop the hero world.

450
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,160
They’re monsters
even among monsters.

451
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:22,600
When that’s our competition,

452
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:24,970
how can we advance
on our own abilities?

453
00:18:25,030 --> 00:18:27,540
What’s wrong
with banding together?

454
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:29,510
Saitama:
I mean, nothing, really.

455
00:18:29,570 --> 00:18:32,440
Still, I think i’ll pass
on your generous offer.

456
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:33,880
Blizzard: You think
you’re too strong for us?

457
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:36,680
Hmph! You’ll never
move up the rankings.

458
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:39,850
Just remember that I
offered you this opportunity.

459
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,120
( Doorbell rings )

460
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:43,790
King: Yo. Saitama here?

461
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,220
( Blizzard gasps )

462
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:46,720
King: Hey, dude.

463
00:18:46,790 --> 00:18:48,490
Did you take my game
home with you?

464
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,990
Blizzard: K-k-k-k-k-king?!

465
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:52,160
Saitama: Oh. Yeah. My bad.

466
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,500
King: I knew it. Hand it over.

467
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,070
Saitama: Uh, sorry, but...

468
00:18:56,130 --> 00:18:58,130
King: It’s no biggie.
Just give it back.

469
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,800
- Saitama: I erased your save.
- King: Wait. What?

470
00:19:00,870 --> 00:19:04,810
Blizzard: Why are they talking
like they’re just friends?

471
00:19:04,870 --> 00:19:07,010
Genos: Master does
not team up with others,

472
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,180
does not antagonize anyone,

473
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,880
- ignores rankings.
- Saitama: ...It was under here.

474
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:12,150
- Sorry.
- King: Nah,

475
00:19:12,210 --> 00:19:13,450
don’t worry about it.

476
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:15,750
Oh, the button’s all smushed in.

477
00:19:15,820 --> 00:19:18,590
Genos: Yet powerful heroes
are drawn to him.

478
00:19:18,650 --> 00:19:21,190
Blizzard: If only
I were one of them.

479
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:23,590
Genos: It is because...

480
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:25,490
He is strong.

481
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:28,760
( Singing in Japanese )

482
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,900
♪

483
00:20:05,970 --> 00:20:10,010
Man: Class s, rank 14, genos
and class b, rank 7, saitama.

484
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:13,780
So then, are we in full
agreement on their hero names?

485
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:14,880
Group: Aye!

486
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:16,610
Man: For slaying
numerous monsters

487
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,880
with steadfast resolve
and dauntless courage,

488
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:21,920
genos’ hero name
will be demon cyborg.

489
00:20:21,980 --> 00:20:23,720
And, based on his appearance,

490
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,090
saitama’s name
will be caped baldy.

491
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:29,890
Man #2: Every aspiring hero
dreams of having a hero name.

492
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:33,130
I’m sure they’ll be elated
to hear theirs. ( Chuckles )

493
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,760
Man #3: Demon cyborg
and caped baldy.

494
00:20:35,830 --> 00:20:38,000
I’m confident those two
will work even harder now.

495
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,900
- ( Sitch growling )
- ( Council laughing )

496
00:20:39,970 --> 00:20:41,670
( Sitch scoffs )

497
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:44,110
Two hours of chitchat
about some useless nicknames,

498
00:20:44,170 --> 00:20:46,280
while the discussion
on how to deal with garou

499
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:48,280
ended in 15 minutes.

500
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:51,210
Damn them
and their Rose-colored glasses.

501
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:53,250
Man #1: Are you referring
to that crazy fellow

502
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,820
who calls himself a monster?

503
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,690
No need to panic, sitch.

504
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:59,050
Man #2: Class s,
rank 3, silverfang

505
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,820
is already in pursuit.

506
00:21:00,890 --> 00:21:03,060
I’m confident in his abilities
on matters like this.

507
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:05,660
Man #3: Yes, I think
we can trust in him.

508
00:21:05,730 --> 00:21:08,130
Man #4: If need be,
tornado and blast can assist.

509
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,100
Man #1: He’s just a man,
sitch, nothing more.

510
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:13,670
He likely has nothing to do
with the prophecy.

511
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:14,970
Sitch: Damn it all!

512
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:18,570
Will they really be enough
to deal with garou?

513
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,040
- ( Whack )
- ( Hero groans )

514
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:22,140
What the hell?

515
00:21:22,210 --> 00:21:24,150
Who--who the hell are you?

516
00:21:24,210 --> 00:21:27,050
I’m a class-a hero,
not a criminal.

517
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,750
Why did you attack me?

518
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:31,950
Garou: Class a, rank 9,
tank-top vegetarian.

519
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:34,120
Because you just happened
to cross my path.

520
00:21:34,190 --> 00:21:36,730
But i’m stunned
by the lack of challenge.

521
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:38,890
Tank-top vegetarian: Then I
suggest you brace yourself.

522
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:42,500
This is what happens
when you tangle with a hero.

523
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,670
- ( Blows lands )
- ( Groans )

524
00:21:44,730 --> 00:21:48,040
Garou: Gotta say,
i’m not impressed.

525
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:50,240
I look forward to finding one

526
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:53,110
who can battle
a monster-class hero.

